    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4932" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κακόω</span></b> , imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κάκου</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐκάκωσα</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bring to evil</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">trouble,
            maltreat, disfigure</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            6.137</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; κεκακωμένοι</span>, ‘in a sad plight,’
            <i><span class="en">Il. 11.689</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; μηδὲ γέροντα κάκου κεκακωμένον</span>,
          ‘afflict the afflicted,’ <i><span class="en">Od.
          4.754</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
